<p class="page" id="a4140305">[Page 305]</p>
<p>Well after we had been standing for two hours &amp; were pretty tired so we were taken to Kes Sl Neh Barracks [Kasr-el-Nil Barracks] where they gave us light refreshments after which we marched back ten miles to camp &amp; made a record doing it in 2 hours &amp; a quarter.<br/>Well Mum Dear the Commanding Officer was so pleased at the discipline &amp; general carriage of the troops that he gave the Battalion general leave for one day. As I am on duty I was not able to have the day off.<br/>Well dear Mum we were told that within the next 6 weeks we will be leaving for Europe. So then we may see something interesting in the shape of war.<br/>You asked me Mother Dear how much I left behind for you the Amount is five shillings per day. So you should get somebody to go to the Barracks &amp; see the Pay master about it my number as you know is 283. B Coy 3rd Batt.<br/>Well dear Mother I hope you &amp; Rube also all the others of my Brothers &amp; Sisters are in the Best of health &amp; happiness</p>
